name.text: Vice Souletric and DJ NuERA - Nu 90s Experience (Chicago)
name.html: Vice Souletric and DJ NuERA - Nu 90s Experience (Chicago)

description.text:
Vice Souletric and Dj NuERA, are bringing a Nu 90s Experience to Chicago!The Nu 90s Experience is more than a show. It is a Hip Hop party celebrating all elements of the culture with non-stop music and live performances, along with DJ and beat sets. The duo bridges the gap between the golden era of rap music and today’s new stars. The tour will be hitting 8 cities and will also feature some of the best regional Hip Hop acts on each stop.Vice Souletric is a an artist and producer who has worked with the likes of Pete Rock, Hi-Tek, Nottz, Talib Kweli, Skyzoo and many more. He has also toured with legend CL Smooth, been nominated for Ohio Hip Hop Awards Album of the year, and most recently released his third studio album, “Vice For President 3,” which features appearances from Benny the Butcher, Young RJ of Slum Village and more.The DJ has always been the backbone of Hip Hop music, and filling that roll for the Nu 90s Experience is DJ NuERA. NuERA is one of hottest and most versatile turntablists coming out of the Midwest, competing in and winning several competitions throughout the United States. NuERA has become an Ambassador of Hip Hop for the Ohio region and continues to grow his brand by curating events focused on dj skill building.Vice Souletric and DJ NuERA will be hitting the Midwest as well as NYC and Washington DC.Nu 90s Experience Promohttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=usC5b485A_QDJ Nu Era DMC Battle Footagehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0mRud3Pjw2kSocial Media/Links

description.html:
Vice Souletric and Dj NuERA, are bringing a Nu 90s Experience to Chicago!

The Nu 90s Experience is more than a show. It is a Hip Hop party celebrating all elements of the culture with non-stop music and live performances, along with DJ and beat sets. The duo bridges the gap between the golden era of rap music and today’s new stars. The tour will be hitting 8 cities and will also feature some of the best regional Hip Hop acts on each stop.

Vice Souletric is a an artist and producer who has worked with the likes of Pete Rock, Hi-Tek, Nottz, Talib Kweli, Skyzoo and many more. He has also toured with legend CL Smooth, been nominated for Ohio Hip Hop Awards Album of the year, and most recently released his third studio album, “Vice For President 3,” which features appearances from Benny the Butcher, Young RJ of Slum Village and more.

The DJ has always been the backbone of Hip Hop music, and filling that roll for the Nu 90s Experience is DJ NuERA. NuERA is one of hottest and most versatile turntablists coming out of the Midwest, competing in and winning several competitions throughout the United States. NuERA has become an Ambassador of Hip Hop for the Ohio region and continues to grow his brand by curating events focused on dj skill building.

Vice Souletric and DJ NuERA will be hitting the Midwest as well as NYC and Washington DC.

description.text:
$7 adv tickets // 21+





DJ noDJ + Terrible Spaceship (Record Release!)





Surprise!! DJ noDJ joins the celebration for Terrible Spaceship's new record, Mechanical Monsters! 





DJ noDJ


DJ noDJ is a six piece band that formed in 2012 around a structured hour-long Daft Punk set. Through hard work and elaborate instrumentation, they now perform genres spanning House, Dub Step, and Hip-Hop, as well as an assortment of other electronic/non electronic dance music. Their style is similar to a DJ- each song flowing seamlessly into the next. To ensure every performance is as unique as it is intimate, DJ noDJ determines their setlist in real time picking deliberately and spontaneously from their curated repertoire of music. 


DJ noDJ brings reimagined renditions of club anthems from artists such as Justice, deadmau5, SBTRKT, and Calvin Harris. Full leading synth lines are topped with modified vocals, samples, a tight rhythm section, and pounding bass creating a multidimensional “DJ set” that will get you on your feet. 


All members currently play or have played in bands with each other (This Must Be The Band, Origin of Animal, Wild Earp) establishing a recognizable musicianship on a professional level. 


Like DJ noDJ on Facebook and follow them on Instagram and Twitter (@DJnoDJchicago), but most importantly, see them live.





TERRIBLE SPACESHIP


Terrible Spaceship, Chicago's finest purveyor of science fiction dance music, will be releasing their third studio album on May 31st at Emporium Wicker Park. This new album, "Mechanical Monsters," will be performed synchronized to a live projection of the 1940's Fleischer Studios "Superman" animations that inspired the music. 





Emporium Arcade Bar - Wicker Park


1366 N Milwaukee Ave


Chicago, IL 60622
www.emporiumchicago.com

description.text: Formerly known and loved as Stars of Tomorrow, Intonation continues its yearly celebration of the youth in its music programs under a new name - Mixtape Live!Bring a blanket, a picnic, and settle in for this all-day FREE community arts extravaganza taking place at Kennicott Park in Chicago’s beautiful Kenwood neighborhood. The stellar line-up includes Intonation’s 20+ youth pop/rock bands and more!The fest will also feature a community dance party, and hands-on activities such as a musical petting zoo, face painting, a photobooth, raffle, and delicious food for purchase. With over 200 students performing, this will once again be the youth arts event of the year!Interested in volunteering? We need your help! Please email jen@intonationmusic.org for more details.Mixtape Live is presented in partnership with Chicago Park District and is part of the programming for Night Out in the Parks.

Formerly known and loved as Stars of Tomorrow, Intonation continues its yearly celebration of the youth in its music programs under a new name - Mixtape Live!

Bring a blanket, a picnic, and settle in for this all-day FREE community arts extravaganza taking place at Kennicott Park in Chicago’s beautiful Kenwood neighborhood. The stellar line-up includes Intonation’s 20+ youth pop/rock bands and more!

The fest will also feature a community dance party, and hands-on activities such as a musical petting zoo, face painting, a photobooth, raffle, and delicious food for purchase. With over 200 students performing, this will once again be the youth arts event of the year!

Interested in volunteering? We need your help! Please email jen@intonationmusic.org for more details.

Mixtape Live is presented in partnership with Chicago Park District and is part of the programming for Night Out in the Parks.
